TITLE: Goats slam sheep over salt lick: Maybe they really are the GOAT
SUMMARY: Two scientists were surprised to see goats and sheep hanging out above the tree line. Turns out they were fighting over patchy salt deposits. They saw 106 "interactions." Guess who almost always won?

SUMMARY: The prestigious award was given to <em>The Seven Moons of Maali Almeida

TITLE: Russia's nuclear arsenal is huge, but will Putin use it?
SUMMARY: Experts in Russian doctrine worry that as the war in Ukraine gets more desperate, Russia might be tempted to detonate a nuclear weapon.

TITLE: You can now apply for Biden's student loan relief plan. Here's how
SUMMARY: "It's easy, it's fast," Biden said in a press conference announcing the launch, noting applications take less than 5 minutes and can be done on desktop or phone.

TITLE: Former NASA astronaut Jim McDivitt, who led Gemini and Apollo missions, dies at 93
SUMMARY: McDivitt commanded two early Gemini and Apollo missions in the 1960s that played a key role in preparing for the moon landing in 1969.

TITLE: Trump hotels charged his Secret Service protectors 'exorbitant' rates
SUMMARY: New documents indicate Trump-owned properties repeatedly charged the Secret Service rates far higher than government rates, as high as $1,185 per room per night.

TITLE: Chelsea Manning shared secrets with WikiLeaks. Now she's telling her own story
SUMMARY: The former military analyst has been called both a hero and a traitor for leaking classified information about the wars in Afghanistan and Iraq. In a new memoir, she talks about why she did it.

TITLE: Emmanuel, a TikTok-famous emu, has avian flu after a deadly outbreak on a Florida farm
SUMMARY: Taylor Blake's family farm in South Florida, Knuckle Bump Farms, has lost 99% of its birds to avian flu. Its most famous resident has suffered nerve damage in his right leg and foot.

TITLE: From the witness stand, Kevin Spacey denies sex abuse claims
SUMMARY: Actor Anthony Rapp says he was a victim of assault and battery. Rapp says Spacey made a sexual advance on him in the 1980s when he was 14 years old.

TITLE: DOJ calls for six-month sentence for Trump ally Steve Bannon
SUMMARY: The Justice Department said in a court filing it wants to see the former Trump adviser sentenced to six months in prison for not complying with the Jan. 6 Committee's investigation.

TITLE: Ukraine war updates: Russia strikes Kyiv as Russian troops move into Belarus (Oct. 17)
SUMMARY: Catch up on key developments and the latest in-depth coverage of Russia's invasion of Ukraine.

TITLE: The capital of Ukraine reels from second Russian attack this month
SUMMARY: At least four people were killed and at least four others have been hospitalized from the drone strike Monday morning.

TITLE: BTS announces upcoming Korean military service
SUMMARY: In June, the mega-popular K-pop group had already announced a hiatus. On Monday, the band's label and management company announced that all seven BTS members will be enlisting in the military.

SUMMARY: Han Solo may be a hunk. But "Pan Solo" is a hunk of bread.
